# Delta Learn Frontend

React 19 + Vite 8 SPA consuming the Django REST backend.

## Architecture

```
Delta-Learn-Frontend/
├── src/
│   ├── api/client.js           # All API calls + JWT token management
│   ├── context/
│   │   ├── ThemeContext.jsx     # Dark/light mode toggle (persisted)
│   │   └── AuthContext.jsx      # JWT auth state, login/register/logout
│   ├── components/
│   │   ├── HomePage.jsx        # Landing page: subject cards, subscribe form
│   │   ├── ChapterView.jsx     # Chapter renderer with Q&A sections
│   │   ├── Sidebar.jsx         # Chapter navigation sidebar
│   │   ├── MermaidDiagram.jsx  # Client-side Mermaid rendering
│   │   ├── AuthModal.jsx       # Login/register modal (React Portal → body)
│   │   ├── HighlightPopup.jsx  # Color picker for text highlights
│   │   ├── NotesDrawer.jsx     # Slide-in notes panel
│   │   ├── HighlightsPage.jsx  # My highlights view
│   │   └── SubscribePage.jsx   # DeltaMails subscription form
│   ├── App.jsx                 # Router + SubjectPage + UserButton
│   ├── App.css                 # All styles (single CSS file)
│   └── main.jsx                # Entry point with BrowserRouter
├── public/
│   ├── favicon.svg             # Delta triangle logo
│   └── _redirects              # Netlify SPA routing
└── index.html                  # Meta tags, OG tags, PWA config
```

## Routing

| Path                        | Component       | Notes                      |
|-----------------------------|-----------------|----------------------------|
| `/`                         | HomePage        | Landing with 3 subject cards |
| `/highlights`               | HighlightsPage  | All user highlights          |
| `/subscribe`                | SubscribePage   | DeltaMails subscription form |
| `/:subject/chapter/:id`    | SubjectPage     | Sidebar + ChapterView       |
| `/:subject`                | SubjectRedirect | Redirects to chapter/1       |

## API Client (`src/api/client.js`)

- `BASE_URL` from `VITE_API_URL` env var, defaults to `http://localhost:8000/api`
- All requests go through `apiFetch()` which auto-attaches JWT Bearer token
- On 401, auto-refreshes the access token using the stored refresh token
- Tokens stored in `localStorage` under key `delta_tokens`

### Available functions
- Public: `fetchSubjects()`, `fetchSubjectDetail(slug)`, `fetchChapter(slug, num)`
- Auth: `register()`, `login()`, `logout()`, `fetchMe()`, `isLoggedIn()`
- Highlights: `fetchHighlights(params)`, `createHighlight(data)`, `deleteHighlight(id)`
- Notes: `fetchNotes(params)`, `createNote(data)`, `updateNote(id, data)`, `deleteNote(id)`, `analyzeNote(id)`
- DeltaMails: `fetchSubscriptions()`, `subscribeDeltaMails(data)`, `updateSubscriptionPreferences(id, data)`, `unsubscribeDeltaMails(data)`

## Design System

### Theme
- Apple-inspired dark mode as default; light mode toggle available
- All colors via CSS custom properties in `:root` / `[data-theme="light"]`
- Per-subject accent color set dynamically via `--accent` on `<html>`

### Subject accent colors
| Subject           | Color   |
|-------------------|---------|
| System Design     | #0a84ff |
| DSA Patterns      | #30d158 |
| AI for Engineers  | #ff9f0a |

## Component Conventions

### Data flow
- `SubjectPage` fetches subject detail + chapter data, passes down as props
- `Sidebar` and `ChapterView` are pure display components (no direct API calls)
- Highlights and notes are fetched in `SubjectPage`, callbacks passed down

### Modal rendering
- `AuthModal` uses `createPortal(jsx, document.body)` to render outside the component tree
- This avoids stacking context issues caused by `backdrop-filter` on parent elements
- All modals should follow this pattern

### Authenticated features
- Wrap with `useAuth()` — check `user` before rendering auth-only UI
- Show "Sign In" button for anonymous users (never block content)
- Highlights: text selection → HighlightPopup → save via API
- Notes: drawer panel, scoped per-chapter or per-subject

## Deployment

- **Netlify**: `npm run build` → `dist/` output
- SPA routing handled by `public/_redirects` (`/* /index.html 200`)
- Set `VITE_API_URL` env var in Netlify to point to PythonAnywhere backend
